A ranar Laraba da ta gabata ne shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana da wani jaridar da aka yi wa China Daily a Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi kowa sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi kasar Sin da yin kokarin tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Peking na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters cewa wani sabon mataki ne a yakin neman zaben Washington na matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje suna yin tallace-tallace don ƙarfafa kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin kasuwanci a yanzu, inda suke daidaita harajin shigo da kayayyaki tsakanin ƙasashe.
A cewar masana na Amurka da China a farkon yakin cinikayya, harajin haraji a kasar Sin an yi niyyar shawo kan masu fitar da kaya a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, wanda ya yi shekaru da yawa yana fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma kamfanoni barazana.
Kasar Sin, in ji Branstad a wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register na Lahadi, "a yanzu tana ninka wannan zalunci ta hanyar tura tallace-tallace a cikin 'yancinmu na buga labarai".
